\begin_layout Subsubsection
Next Steps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To date, we have no indication that any of the beetles which died in the
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

witch's brew
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 experiment were killed by OrNV.
 We sent gut samples from beetles which died in the experiments to Dr.
 Marshall for virus detection.
 If any virus is detected, we will resume iterations of the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

witch's brew
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 experiment in an attempt to increase virulence.
 Analysis of the gut samples is awaiting finalization of a contract between
 UOG and AgResearch supported by Farm Bill FY2017 funds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We have also trapped a series of beetles and dissected out guts to send
 to Ag Research for virus detection.
 Biological control agents often arrive a few years after detection of invasive
 species.
 These 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fortuitous introductions
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 are common.
 These samples have been sent to AgResearch and analysis is also pending
 finalization of a new contract.
\end_layout

