\begin_layout Paragraph
Collaboration with CRB Researchers University of Hawaii 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
During a trip to Guam by University of Hawaii researchers Drs.
 Mike Melzer, Shizu Watanabe and Zhiqiang Cheng we visited a Home Depot
 hardware store to investigate claims that they were selling bags of soil
 prepopulated with CRB.
 Our findings were documented as a scientific note 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "moore_movement_2016"

\end_inset

.
 During April, 2017 live CRB grubs and adults were accidentally shipped
 from Guam to Saipan in a shipment of packaged soil purchased from Home
 Depot.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
On my way back to Guam from the International Congress of Entomology, I
 met with colleagues at UH-Manoa to discuss and participate in coconut rhinocero
s beetle research: Mike Melzer, Shizu Watanabe, Zhiqiang Cheng, Dan Jenkins,
 John Allen, Hans Ramm, Mitch McLean.
 Discussed collaboration on development of instrumentation.
 Photos from a lab session available here: 
